# SPIKE: env for the Docker dev stack. Copy to `.env` and fill in.
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# Compose auto-loads `.env` from this directory. These are the same secrets the
# host flow expects in client/.env.local and sync-worker/.dev.vars — here we keep
# them in one place. Both files are gitignored; this stack reads the secrets via
# the bind-mounted repo (sync-worker auto-loads its .dev.vars) and via the vars
# below for the client.
#
# You need a Clerk publishable + secret key (see apps/dotcom/README.md).

# --- client (Vite, baked into the browser bundle) ---
VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=

# --- sync-worker (.dev.vars, read by wrangler) ---
# NOTE: the sync-worker reads CLERK_* from apps/dotcom/sync-worker/.dev.vars on
# the host (bind-mounted in). Create that file as the host flow already requires:
#   CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=...
#   CLERK_SECRET_KEY=...
